  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      ICU patients do experience extubation failure. Guidelines rarely include muscle strength
      criteria. Prior work indicates that grip strength is a reliable surrogate for muscle
      strength. The purpose of the study is to assess the success rate of mechanical ventilation
      weaning based on the grip test.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
